I took an extremely brief look at this issue; slapped my forehead; of course, mappings just throw stuff into a input queue. Who knows where it came from?

@justinmk This issue reminds of a comment you made elsewhere, that might offer a way to address this issue.

> Part of the work to implement "multicursor" support will be to "atomize" input so that its structure is exposed.
